-- German States Seek a Share of Nuclear Power Tax, FT Deutschland Reports
-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 2010-10-15T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/german-states-seek-a-share-of-nuclear-power-tax-ft-deutschland-reports.html
Germany’s federal states will seek a
share today of a nuclear tax expected to generate 2.3 billion
euros ($3.23 billion) annually,  Financial Times Deutschland 
reported, citing a report obtained from an unnamed source.  States led by Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s Christian
Democrats will join Lower Saxony and Schleswig-Holstein in
demanding a stake in the tax at today’s meeting of the Federal
Assembly, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Naomi Kresge  in Berlin at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.netnet  